# {{alternative spelling of|[[bonnet]]}}
# A bunnet or bunnit is a specific style [[flat]] [[sport]]ing [[cap]] made from [[wool]] or a wool blend that is common with farmers and country gentlemen in cooler areas of the planet that experience higher than normal rainfall such as Scotland (where it originated), the British Isles, New Zealand etc.
# A flat cap, traditionally made of wool.



====Usage notes====
Under the name bunnet, the flat cap is often associated with the working class in the northern UK. The tam o'shanter is similar, but has a toorie, or pompom, on its center.

